v:ud.v:prompt: Determines how member shapes are aligned in list (0 = Left; 1 = Center; 2 = Right for vertical lists. 0 = Top; 1 = Middle; 2 = Bottom for horizontal lists.)
Direction that list arranges member shapes (0 = Left to Right; 1 = Right to Left; 2 = Top to Bottom; 3 = Bottom to Top)
Distance between list members
Name or UniqueID of master shape to instance on Insert commands. Value must be placed inside a USE() function.
Boolean value that prevents reordering of members. The list must also be locked via User.msvSDContainerLocked = True for setting to have any effect.
Semi-colon delimited list of category names. Other shapes must have at least one matching name to be allowed as list members.
Semi-colon delimited list of category names. Other shapes with at least one matching name are disallowed as list members.

v:ud.v:val: VT4(List Container Width: Allthough growing width is readily supported, shrinking width is a little more tricky when there is more than one child container. Setps: 1) Lock the parent list container 2) Select all the child containers and resize smaller 3) Unlock the parent list container 4) Make a slight adjustment with one of the child containers This will adjust the parent list container smaller to match the widest child container. Context Menu: The Flag > Lock Container will allow child shapes e.g. containers to get the primary focus. This will allow shapes to be dropped on to the child shape, rather than adding to the List Container.)
